{
  "data": {
    "book": {
      "commonName": "Genesis",
      "firstChapterApiLink": "/api/BSB/GEN/1.json",
      "id": "GEN",
      "lastChapterApiLink": "/api/BSB/GEN/50.json",
      "name": "Genesis",
      "numberOfChapters": 50,
      "order": 1,
      "sha256": "9ae507188093d846873e8affd9e88c21ac55abdbc6d8adb9beb220345494f0f1",
      "title": "Genesis",
      "totalNumberOfVerses": 1533,
      "translationId": "BSB"
    },
    "chapter": {
      "content": [
        {
          "content": [
            "Cain and Abel"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And Adam had relations with his wife Eve, and she conceived and gave birth to Cain.",
            {
              "noteId": 4332
            },
            {
              "lineBreak": true
            },
            "“With the help of the LORD I have brought forth a man,” she said."
          ],
          "number": 1,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Later she gave birth to Cain’s brother Abel.",
            {
              "lineBreak": true
            },
            "Now Abel was a keeper of sheep, while Cain was a tiller of the soil."
          ],
          "number": 2,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So in the course of time, Cain brought some of the fruit of the soil as an offering to the LORD,"
          ],
          "number": 3,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "while Abel brought the best portions of the firstborn of his flock.",
            {
              "lineBreak": true
            },
            "And the LORD looked with favor on Abel and his offering,"
          ],
          "number": 4,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "but He had no regard for Cain and his offering. So Cain became very angry, and his countenance fell."
          ],
          "number": 5,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "“Why are you angry,” said the LORD to Cain, “and why has your countenance fallen?"
          ],
          "number": 6,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "If you do what is right, will you not be accepted? But if you refuse to do what is right, sin is crouching at your door; it desires you,",
            {
              "noteId": 4333
            },
            "but you must master it.”"
          ],
          "number": 7,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Then Cain said to his brother Abel, “Let us go out to the field.”",
            {
              "noteId": 4334
            },
            "And while they were in the field, Cain rose up against his brother Abel and killed him."
          ],
          "number": 8,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And the LORD said to Cain, “Where is your brother Abel?”",
            {
              "lineBreak": true
            },
            "“I do not know!” he answered. “Am I my brother’s keeper?”"
          ],
          "number": 9,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "“What have you done?” replied the LORD. “The voice of your brother’s blood cries out to Me from the ground."
          ],
          "number": 10,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Now you are cursed and banished from the ground, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother’s blood from your hand."
          ],
          "number": 11,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "When you till the ground, it will no longer yield its produce to you. You will be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth.”"
          ],
          "number": 12,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "But Cain said to the LORD, “My punishment",
            {
              "noteId": 4335
            },
            "is greater than I can bear."
          ],
          "number": 13,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Behold, this day You have driven me from the face of the earth, and from Your face I will be hidden; I will be a fugitive and a wanderer on the earth, and whoever finds me will kill me.”"
          ],
          "number": 14,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "“Not so!”",
            {
              "noteId": 4336
            },
            "replied the LORD. “If anyone slays Cain, then Cain will be avenged sevenfold.” And the LORD placed a mark on Cain, so that no one who found him would kill him."
          ],
          "number": 15,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "So Cain went out from the presence of the LORD and settled in the land of Nod,",
            {
              "noteId": 4337
            },
            "east of Eden."
          ],
          "number": 16,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "The Descendants of Cain"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And Cain had relations with his wife, and she conceived and gave birth to Enoch. Then Cain built a city and named it after his son Enoch."
          ],
          "number": 17,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Now to Enoch was born Irad, and Irad was the father of Mehujael, and Mehujael was the father of Methusael, and Methusael was the father of Lamech."
          ],
          "number": 18,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And Lamech married two women, one named Adah and the other Zillah."
          ],
          "number": 19,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Adah gave birth to Jabal; he was the father of those who dwell in tents and raise livestock."
          ],
          "number": 20,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And his brother’s name was Jubal; he was the father of all who play the harp and flute."
          ],
          "number": 21,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And Zillah gave birth to Tubal-cain, a forger of every implement of bronze and iron. And the sister of Tubal-cain was Naamah."
          ],
          "number": 22,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Then Lamech said to his wives:",
            {
              "lineBreak": true
            },
            {
              "poem": 1,
              "text": "“Adah and Zillah, hear my voice;"
            },
            {
              "poem": 2,
              "text": "wives of Lamech, listen to my speech."
            },
            {
              "poem": 1,
              "text": "For I have slain a man for wounding me,"
            },
            {
              "poem": 2,
              "text": "a young man for striking me."
            }
          ],
          "number": 23,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "poem": 1,
              "text": "If Cain is avenged sevenfold,"
            },
            {
              "poem": 2,
              "text": "then Lamech seventy-sevenfold.”"
            },
            {
              "noteId": 4338
            }
          ],
          "number": 24,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "Seth and Enosh"
          ],
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And Adam again had relations with his wife, and she gave birth to a son and named him Seth,",
            {
              "noteId": 4339
            },
            "saying, “God has granted me another seed in place of Abel, since Cain killed him.”"
          ],
          "number": 25,
          "type": "verse"
        },
        {
          "type": "line_break"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            "And to Seth also a son was born, and he called him Enosh.",
            {
              "lineBreak": true
            },
            "At that time men began to call upon",
            {
              "noteId": 4340
            },
            "the name of the LORD."
          ],
          "number": 26,
          "type": "verse"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4332,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 1
          },
          "text": "Cain sounds like the Hebrew for acquired or brought forth."
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4333,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 7
          },
          "text": "Or it desires to control you"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4334,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 8
          },
          "text": "SP, LXX, Syriac, and Vulgate; Hebrew Then Cain spoke to his brother Abel."
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4335,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 13
          },
          "text": "Or guilt or sin"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4336,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 15
          },
          "text": "LXX, Vulgate, and Syriac; Hebrew “Very well!” or “Therefore:”"
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4337,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 16
          },
          "text": "Nod means wandering."
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4338,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 24
          },
          "text": "Hebrew; LXX can be translated as either seventy times seven or seventy-sevenfold; see also Matthew 18:22."
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4339,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 25
          },
          "text": "Seth probably means granted or appointed."
        },
        {
          "caller": "+",
          "noteId": 4340,
          "reference": {
            "chapter": 4,
            "verse": 26
          },
          "text": "Or to proclaim; some translators to invoke or to call themselves by or to profane"
        }
      ],
      "number": 4
    },
